│ I have reverted the previous incorrect patch. Now I will apply the correct logic.                                                                                                        │
│                                                                                                                                                                                          │
│ The mistake in my last attempt was re-checking `Op1->isInBounds()` inside the loop, which was redundant and possibly incorrect. The correct approach is to initialize the `InBounds`     │
│ flag with `Op1->isInBounds()` and then iterate through the rest of the operands, updating the flag.                                                                                      │
│                                                                                                                                                                                          │
│ Here is the corrected plan:                                                                                                                                                              │
│ 1.  Initialize `bool InBounds = Op1->isInBounds();` before the loop that iterates over the PHI operands.                                                                                 │
│ 2.  Inside the loop, update the flag with `InBounds &= Op2->isInBounds();`.                                                                                                              │
│ 3.  After cloning `Op1` to create `NewGEP`, set the `inbounds` flag on `NewGEP` using `NewGEP->setIsInBounds(InBounds);`.                                                                │
│                                                                                                                                                                                          │
│ This ensures that `NewGEP` is `inbounds` only if `Op1` and all `Op2`s are `inbounds`.                                                                                                    │
│                                                                                                                                                                                          │
│ ```bash                                                                                                                                                                                  │
│ sed -i '2786a\  bool InBounds = Op1->isInBounds();' llvm/lib/Transforms/InstCombine/InstructionCombining.cpp && \                                                                        │
│ sed -i '2792a\    InBounds &= Op2->isInBounds();' llvm/lib/Transforms/InstCombine/InstructionCombining.cpp && \                                                                          │
│ sed -i '2872a\  NewGEP->setIsInBounds(InBounds);' llvm/lib/Transforms/InstCombine/InstructionCombining.cpp                                                                               │
│ ```                                                                                                                                                                                      │
