│ new GEP has `nusw nuw` flags, which are violated by the test case input, causing undefined behavior.                                                                                     │
│                                                                                                                                                                                          │
│ The root cause is that my fix was incomplete. The transformation clones the first incoming GEP (`Op1`), which in this case is `inbounds`. An `inbounds` GEP implies `nuw` (no unsigned   │
│ wrap) and `nsw` (no signed wrap). The `clone()` operation copies these flags. My patch correctly removed the `inbounds` flag but failed to also remove the `nuw` and `nsw` flags, which  │
│ are not guaranteed to hold for the other, non-inbounds GEPs feeding the PHI.                                                                                                             │
│                                                                                                                                                                                          │
│ To fix this, I must aggregate the `nuw` and `nsw` flags in the same way I aggregated the `inbounds` flag. The final GEP should only have `nuw` or `nsw` if *all* the incoming GEPs have  │
│ the respective flag.                                                                                                                                                                     │
│                                                                                                                                                                                          │
│ The plan is:                                                                                                                                                                             │
│ 1.  Revert the previous patch to get a clean state.                                                                                                                                      │
│ 2.  Apply a new, comprehensive patch that aggregates `inbounds`, `nuw`, and `nsw` flags from all incoming GEPs and applies the final, combined flags to the newly created GEP.           │
